Confession time… 
So I’m in my mid 20s now..but I’m not sure about this whole adulting thing. Womanhood is full of challenges.. shoot life is full of trial and tribulations, and I can’t lie.. a lot of days I feel the burn. I am doing my best to keep FAITH. It feels like I’m on the right path, but a lot of hurt and disappointment has tried to destroy me. Thank you God for keeping Me and renewing me Still✌🏽 I NEED You.

Not crazy about any of the pics from this night but one thing is for sure… This message is right on brand.

Do you ever feel like life can be really hard and difficult? I’m sure a lot of you ladies are like me.. in that you feel like it shouldn’t have to be this hard.. or maybe you wish some rich body would come give you all of their money so you could stop constantly working…
 Some days are a breeze and others feel like a constant battle. The Bible says, “in this life we will have trials and tribulations.” Once I started accepting this principal in life as truth- as true as the principle of gravity- I have found life to seem “more fair” oddly enough. Haha. Don’t lie to yourself, keep the faith, embrace the grind .. bc one day you’ll look up on the other side and suddenly you’re a 💎

I am so grateful for all of the highs and lows of 2023! 🥂 
The self growth was so real. I learned so many lessons it would take me so long to write every one of them, but some of my biggest take aways of the year were
1. MY VALUE 
2. Connections: Showing up for the people who show up for you, that our decisions have consequences on the ones you love so make decisions that honor them and this ultimately will serve you back. I’m so grateful for the people in my corner who allow me to feel celebrated, not tolerated. My family, friends, and Asha are my whole heart ❤️ 
2. I LOVE to uplift  and heal others, especially through creative outlets. 
3. Way More responsibility 🙃 consistency, discipline, and working for heart and integrity, rather than a dollar amount. 

It wasn’t easy folks, but we survived! 

2024 is our year!!
